# Application code — Claude Code only

**Default: DO NOT EDIT these files in Cursor.**

Application code is shipped by **Claude Code** on `executor: claude-code` ticket branches (`./scripts/ticket run`).

## Allowed in Cursor (without extra permission)

- Read / search / explain / review
- Point to lines in critique or handoff specs

## Forbidden unless user explicitly says "Cursor implement this code"

- Any patch under `apps/website/internal/`, `apps/website/frontend/src/`, `apps/mod/`
- "Fixing" audit findings (C1, C2, etc.) yourself
- Completing plan todos that say `claude-code`

## If the user wants a fix

1. Write or update ticket + `.ai/artifacts/tXXX_claude_code_handoff.md`
2. Tell user to paste handoff into Claude Code

## Exception

`executor: cursor-docs` slices that only touch docs under `docs/` or registry — still **no** app source edits.
